The Science and Technology Minister says they are focusing on growing the economy and giving young people entrepreneurship opportunities. CAPE TOWN – Cabinet minister Naledi Pandor says that the new administration will remain committed to addressing matters of job creation in South Africa. The Science and Technology Minister says that they are focusing on growing the economy and giving young people entrepreneurship opportunities. Pandor says that while she's looking forward to State of the Nation Address today, she isn't certain yet about her future. “As to the Cabinet, that’s entirely his decision and one has no idea whatsoever but wherever one is sent to serve, one would try and serve out country.”